Hello Yinz! (Pittsburghese for you all)

I'm a creative marketer, photographer and content specialist based in, you guessed it, Pittsburgh PA. I specialize in creating content both written and visual, as well as helping clients understand how their entire ecosystem of content defines their brand experience. I love nothing more than helping strategize, conceptualize and then execute a content plan.

I'm currently looking for my next full-time opportunity and freelancing on the side. You can check out some of my work <https://www.davedinuzzo.com|here>, or find me on <https://www.linkedin.com/in/dave-dinuzzo/|LinkedIn>. Happy Monday everyone!

Hi folks - I come to content marketing from the writing and content management side. I was a freelance writer (ESPN, Deadspin, Seattle-based newspapers and mags), Executive Editor of a magazine. I managed video, web, and newsletter content for Allrecipes, and have been Creative Director at the CM firm Content Harmony since 2017. I believe that strong writing and storytelling are table stakes for successful content marketing .— but can be very hard to operationalize  I’m here to see how others drive successful content operations and share any advice that might be helpful to others.

attachments.title: I Bought My Ticket But The Game Was Gone: Pearl Jam And The SuperSonics, 1990-2008
attachments.text: If you were going to pick a day to be a fly on the wall, you could do a lot worse than Oct. 8, 1990, in the dank downtown Seattle basement-cum-rehearsal space where Eddie Vedder, having arrived on a plane from California that morning, sang with Pearl Jam for the first time.
